1
00:00:01,680 --> 00:00:04,520
What? You bastard.

2
00:00:06,420 --> 00:00:08,130
Trash?

3
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:14,450
Yeah,
because you're blaming me for what you did.

4
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:19,520
Tell me truthfully what happened.

5
00:00:33,940 --> 00:00:37,020
Sorry. My words were a bit harsh, weren't they?

6
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,780
I'm shocked because it's the first time I've ever been accused of doing something like this.

7
00:00:46,330 --> 00:00:48,350
It's really nothing.

8
00:00:52,090 --> 00:00:55,550
Episode 2:
The moment you want to run away

9
00:00:56,250 --> 00:01:01,280
Why isn't Choi Joon Woo coming after saying he would?

10
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:03,510
I have to get off of work.

11
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,290
Joon Woo.

12
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:08,440
You can be honest with me.

13
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:11,470
The truth is, I already knew.

14
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:18,050
- Hey, where did the teacher's watch go? It was just here.
- He must've worn it out.

15
00:01:18,050 --> 00:01:21,030
- He wasn't wearing it though.
- Did you see it on him?

16
00:01:21,030 --> 00:01:23,910
- You should have told him.
- I was just trying to prank Song Joon Yeong.

17
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:26,310
I was going to hide it.

18
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:30,530
It's that kid isn't it.

19
00:01:30,530 --> 00:01:32,990
It was that delivery guy.
The punk took it.

20
00:01:32,990 --> 00:01:37,170
- No way.
- What do you mean, no way? I saw him before pretending to clean up and he was fooling with it.

21
00:01:37,170 --> 00:01:38,240
This jerk--

22
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,450
Sang Hoon, I'll go instead.

23
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:41,720
Let go.

24
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:45,100
I'll go and see. He's from my class.

25
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:49,530
Hey Joon Woo, hold on.

26
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:52,130
I thought of it then.

27
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:56,500
Let's not worsen a situation which already happened.

28
00:01:56,500 --> 00:02:00,170
Instead, let's find a way to help you.

29
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:04,270
Hey idiot. Do you really think he would just leave it there?

30
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:07,200
He would've hidden it already in his pockets or pants.

31
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,640
He's not a person who would do that.

32
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:12,820
What do you mean not? You said he was forcibly transferred to our school because he stole at his last school.

33
00:02:12,820 --> 00:02:15,510
The rumors have already spread.

34
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,700
No wonder he looked a little off.

35
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,090
But...

36
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:23,270
It seems that Jo Sang Hoon in class 1 told everything to the teachers.

37
00:02:23,270 --> 00:02:25,580
Even the fact that I knew everything.

38
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,610
Jo Sang Hoon.

39
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:33,360
Sorry, Joon Woo. I didn't think things would go this far.

40
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,700
But...

41
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,850
- Instead, you suspect me—
- Suspect?

42
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:48,080
It's not suspicion.

43
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:50,170
I saw everything.

44
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:53,570
What are you saying?

45
00:02:55,090 --> 00:02:58,300
I thought you would have a reason.

46
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:06,150
You must have a reason even for how you're acting right now, too.

47
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:12,590
Hey! Choi Joon Woo!

48
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:18,820
Is that you Joon Woo? You must submit a written apology, but you're not coming. Why aren't you even answering my calls?

49
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:20,570
Come quickly.

50
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,490
Come quickly! Hurry!

51
00:03:24,670 --> 00:03:27,000
Are you going to tell the sub homeroom teacher

52
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,620
what you're thinking?

53
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:37,950
Who knows?

54
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:04,550
Lee Gi Tae

55
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,130
You will be connected to the voicemail...

56
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:10,230
What are you doing? Not picking up.

57
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:18,600
Are you okay?

58
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:21,670
It must hurt.

59
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:24,570
You didn't go to the academy?

60
00:04:24,570 --> 00:04:28,250
How could I go when you are like this?

61
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,690
Letter of Apology

62
00:04:39,060 --> 00:04:41,770
No matter how much I think about it, I don't have anything to reflect on.

63
00:04:41,770 --> 00:04:44,590
Omg. Hey you—

64
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:47,680
I didn't expect this.

65
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:51,020
You have talent! You expressed the ladybug well, but still,

66
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:54,220
let's rewrite this so we can submit something.

67
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:56,820
I'll get in trouble if you submit like this.

68
00:04:57,570 --> 00:04:59,760
But I really don't have anything to write.

69
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:04,010
And your transfer will be on hold.

70
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:05,640
Hey, Joon Woo,

71
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:09,310
As you know, I'm a substitute homeroom teacher.

72
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:14,720
Big cases like this happening while I'm here and a transfer student transferring again,

73
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:18,140
the students are becoming distracted and following instructions less and less.

74
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:20,810
If this continues, how would this make me look?

75
00:05:20,810 --> 00:05:23,930
Please just think of it simply.

76
00:05:23,930 --> 00:05:26,560
A transfer student is just moving again because of his situation.

77
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,990
No, no, the reality of things isn't processed like that.

78
00:05:29,990 --> 00:05:34,440
Ok, Joon Woo, first, with the reflection—

79
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,930
A reflection is not a drawing but

80
00:05:37,930 --> 00:05:40,980
with writing...Wait, why did this come out?

81
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:43,190
So let's quickly...

82
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:45,440
Joon Woo.

83
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:48,470
Choi Joon Woo!

84
00:05:53,370 --> 00:05:55,530
Hey! Choi Joon Woo.

85
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:59,860
Please, let's just write a reflection.

86
00:06:04,940 --> 00:06:08,770
Hey! Hurry up and come here, Joon Woo!

87
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:12,770
Oh, it's so hot and it hurts so much...

88
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:16,970
Yes, good thinking. Here.

89
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,900
That's right. Come here.

90
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:26,620
Yeah.

91
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:29,200
After all, Oh Han Gyeol is just a temporary replacement.

92
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:32,030
Hey! Choi Joon Woo!

93
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:36,990
Hey, Jo Sang Hoon. Do you know what happens when you just trust your smarts and don't put in any effort?

94
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:39,430
You get dumber, punk.

95
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:42,620
Even if you become dumber, you're still better than Hui Yeong in math.

96
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:46,230
Don't be like that. How can you be so obvious about your bias?

97
00:06:46,230 --> 00:06:50,520
There's no way he'd get it wrong. He got it wrong because he knew it was a misdeed.

98
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:52,720
It's not fair.

99
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:58,930
Hui Yeong.

100
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,100
Are you okay?

101
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:08,870
But hey, wasn't Ma Hui Yeong a little 'cringey' earlier?

102
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:12,760
"I just hope that even if it's just us that we don't have prejudice toward Joon Woo."

103
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:16,440
"We should believe him and become his strength."

104
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:20,020
Hey, if you keep going you'll get in trouble with Soo Bin.

105
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,430
Why would I?

106
00:07:21,430 --> 00:07:24,960
I told you Hui Yeong is not my boyfriend. We were just pre-K school classmates.

107
00:07:27,330 --> 00:07:32,120
But I do agree with what he said before.

108
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:35,970
Maybe we should've found a way to help out Choi Joon Woo.

109
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:38,670
I've thought about that too.

110
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:43,540
Why am I so pretty?

111
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:46,230
What the.

112
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:50,230
- Wow. Yoo Soo Bin, daebak.
- What?

113
00:07:50,230 --> 00:07:52,320
You look so pretty Soo Bin.

114
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,830
What time is it right now?

115
00:08:02,830 --> 00:08:05,370
Yoo Soo Bin, do you want to keep being like this?

116
00:08:05,370 --> 00:08:08,680
Do you know how much the tutor my friend introduced me to costs?

117
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:12,270
If you don't go today that tutor goes out the door.

118
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:15,360
Yoo Soo Bin. Hey!

119
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,440
My mom, seriously.

120
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:19,500
Is there something going on?

121
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,030
You get tutoring? Math?

122
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:24,190
Who?
How much?

123
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:28,200
I really don't want to but my mom...

124
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:32,170
I should get going. See you tomorrow!

125
00:08:32,170 --> 00:08:36,750
- Bye Soo Bin!
- Go well! Stop front-end colliding with your mom! (fighting)

126
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:42,230
Doing well in school seems so tiring, right?

127
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,920
My mom totally gave up on me.

128
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:48,170
She's just thankful that I attend school.

129
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:50,940
I'm going to get going too.

130
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:53,220
But don't you get tutored today Romi?

131
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:55,500
Going to a spa with my mom.

132
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:58,670
Bye.

133
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:02,230
Please Mom, I really don't want to get tutored.

134
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:05,290
- I'll just work really hard by myself.
- Is that what working hard looks like?

135
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:08,040
So when are you going to stop being second tier in math?

136
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,760
But Mom.

137
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:13,200
If you keep being like this, I'm going to find Hui Yeong's mom

138
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:17,360
- so you can get in his math academy.
- No, don't do that. I'll just go.

139
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:20,040
Be there in ten minutes, you dare be even a minute late.

140
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,830
How can I get there in ten minutes?

141
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:24,170
Why can't you be there in ten minutes?

142
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:27,540
The officetel is right by the school. Are you not at school right now?

143
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:31,250
No, you're right I'm at school.

144
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:33,430
Bye.

145
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,820
Seriously...I really hate this.

146
00:09:38,170 --> 00:09:42,270
There's not a student that tutor has taught that hasn't gotten into Seoul National University.

147
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:46,070
Career is very important for her.

148
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:54,940
I'm in late! I won't be there in ten minutes. Ah...

149
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:03,370
You!

150
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:04,820
Yeah.

151
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:09,490
Hey! Where are you going right now?

152
00:10:09,490 --> 00:10:11,940
- Part-time job.
- Is it far?

153
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,400
Oh your already there.

154
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,390
Turn it around.

155
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:23,120
I have something really important so I'll just borrow this.

156
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,180
You can't, my house is far away.

157
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,810
I promise to return it. Sorry!

158
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:32,320
I have to go home later and it's far away!

159
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:36,020
Sorry!

160
00:10:36,930 --> 00:10:39,490
It's really far though.

161
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:44,770
Your mother said that Seoul National University was your goal.

162
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:49,050
Right, that's my mother's ideal scenario.

163
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:53,720
I'll just be thankful to be accepted with the major I want.

164
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:58,360
So you should work harder and make Seoul National University your goal like your mother--.

165
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:03,040
But I know, Teacher, that it won't happen even if I try.

166
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:06,080
I'm not that great intellectually.

167
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:11,070
I also don't want to be stressed out by making unrealistic goals for myself.

168
00:11:13,970 --> 00:11:17,710
Still, I've already discussed this with your mother.

169
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:19,860
Teacher,

170
00:11:19,860 --> 00:11:24,410
I've heard from all your previous students that you were a wonderful teacher

171
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:27,130
who helped them all get into Seoul National University.

172
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:30,010
I don't want you to needlessly stain your

173
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:34,850
perfect record just because of me.

174
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:42,800
I will try to convince my mom to forget about it tonight.

175
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,950
Thank you for taking the time to meet with me.

176
00:11:45,950 --> 00:11:49,030
Yes, Soo Bin, you did well.

177
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,960
Did he get off work already?

178
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:41,450
Oh, you scared me.

179
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:45,800
- What are you doing here?
- I wanted to see what you were looking at.

180
00:12:48,780 --> 00:12:50,260
This.

181
00:13:11,830 --> 00:13:17,460
Thank you for earlier. I was actually just playing with my friends and skipped study hall.

182
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:20,800
But my mom called urgently, so I had to go.

183
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,540
Thanks, for returning it.

184
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:25,880
Goodbye.

185
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,590
Hey, did you really think I'd just keep it?

186
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:33,720
If I couldn't meet you today, I was going to return it at school tomorrow.

187
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:39,630
I'm not coming tomorrow.

188
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:41,830
Didn't you say you would come until tomorrow?

189
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:44,950
I'm just not coming.

190
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:14,020
Is this what you call doing research?

191
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:19,060
I worked hard on it.

192
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:23,570
References are not only titles of books and the names of authors.

193
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:26,900
Here, I also wrote publishers.

194
00:14:27,570 --> 00:14:32,260
You must specify where the quote comes from in the texts.

195
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:34,890
You've never done this before?

196
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:38,490
Anyway,

197
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:42,550
redo it by tomorrow.

198
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,820
I said I won't go starting tomorrow.

199
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:51,500
That's your business. Whether you come or not, shouldn't you take full responsibility of your part?

200
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:56,200
I took responsibility for my actions and came here to return your bike.

201
00:14:56,200 --> 00:15:01,210
You weren't planning on hanging us out to dry
like an irresponsible person, were you?

202
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:05,060
You heard that I'm the queen of evaluation, right?

203
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:10,940
If I took you into our team,
you should have the courtesy to— Whoa!

204
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:25,320
Here, the eyes.

205
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:30,820
Is something in your eye?
Let me see.

206
00:15:34,530 --> 00:15:37,420
I'll look at your eye for you.

207
00:15:37,420 --> 00:15:40,110
No, not me.

208
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,650
Here.

209
00:15:53,050 --> 00:15:55,500
He should've told me sooner.

210
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:11,790
H-Hey, I have something I want to ask you.

211
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:18,520
Please, a One Day pack.

212
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:24,860
I'll go first.

213
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,850
Thanks for the bike.

214
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:30,260
What is it...
that you're curious about?

215
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,970
Um...

216
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:39,150
Did you really...

217
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:41,900
steal the teacher's watch?

218
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:50,230
Never mind, I don't think so.

219
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:52,260
I'll go now.

220
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:53,910
Why?

221
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:58,380
Why do you think I didn't?

222
00:17:05,020 --> 00:17:07,990
I thought you had a situation come up.

223
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,350
That there must be a reason for you being like this now, too.

224
00:17:15,450 --> 00:17:18,050
Hui Yeong is studying right now.

225
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,360
Father, did you come?

226
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:28,600
What have you been doing, huh?

227
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,220
You look awkward standing like this.

228
00:17:33,450 --> 00:17:36,800
You still can't sit and wait patiently?

229
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:40,160
- No. I was looking for my workbook—
- Where's your report card?

230
00:17:40,940 --> 00:17:44,480
- It comes out tomorrow.
- Hui Yeong said he did really well.

231
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,390
You know him, right?
The son of Department Head Jo?

232
00:17:47,390 --> 00:17:50,640
Jo Sang Hoon, in class 1.

233
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:53,780
Yes, Jo Sang Hoon.
The smart one.

234
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:57,570
You, be careful of guys like him.

235
00:17:57,570 --> 00:18:02,080
The commoners who have only brains and nothing else.
They are the scariest.

236
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:06,210
That's me, too.
I had nothing but my brain to reply on

237
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,790
in order to climb to the top.

238
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:10,820
Not more, not less.

239
00:18:10,820 --> 00:18:14,050
Just do as much as your brother did, okay?

240
00:18:14,050 --> 00:18:15,390
Yes, sir.

241
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,000
What's this?

242
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,660
Open up.
Open this door!

243
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:51,460
Open it. Hey!

244
00:18:57,840 --> 00:19:02,120
Do you know how hard I worked
to get you that teacher?

245
00:19:02,990 --> 00:19:04,620
Why are you doing what you want to do?

246
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:07,290
I feel uncomfortable in those one-on-one meetings.

247
00:19:07,290 --> 00:19:08,900
Are you seriously...

248
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:11,750
Are you at a time when
you can decide to be comfortable or uncomfortable?

249
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,690
Just look at your grades.

250
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:18,090
What's wrong with my grades?
Twenty-eighth in the whole school isn't that bad.

251
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:23,090
Parents in other households would praise their kids
if they took home the same results.

252
00:19:23,090 --> 00:19:27,020
Are you the same as other households?
If you look at the ones in Seoul University,

253
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:29,700
