00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:30,670
That's big trouble. Girls that are so pretty.
They prevent boys from studying.

508
00:44:33,060 --> 00:44:35,120
Thank you.

509
00:44:36,150 --> 00:44:41,410
So, you want her to join Teacher Son Jae Yeong's class?

510
00:44:41,410 --> 00:44:45,370
Yes.
No matter how hard I looked,

511
00:44:45,370 --> 00:44:48,180
there are no math teachers like Teacher Son Jae Yeong.

512
00:44:48,180 --> 00:44:49,160
That's true.

513
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:53,860
I talked to him and he said he needed your permission.

514
00:44:53,860 --> 00:44:56,100
It's too much!

515
00:44:56,100 --> 00:45:00,360
What's this about getting my permission.
If you have the ability, then do it.

516
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:03,520
You know you have to take a level test.

517
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:05,430
Of course.

518
00:45:05,430 --> 00:45:07,200
I...

519
00:45:08,490 --> 00:45:10,830
- Nevertheless...
- Nevertheless...

520
00:45:10,830 --> 00:45:16,530
We all know that nothing can be done
without your permission.

521
00:45:16,530 --> 00:45:18,290
I'll count on you, Madame.

522
00:45:18,290 --> 00:45:20,500
So, I will speak to him.

523
00:45:20,500 --> 00:45:22,220
I'm thankful.

524
00:45:22,220 --> 00:45:23,410
I'm home.

525
00:45:23,410 --> 00:45:27,210
You came, Son?
Soo Bin and her mom are here.

526
00:45:27,210 --> 00:45:29,310
- Hello.
- Hi, Hui Yeong.

527
00:45:29,310 --> 00:45:32,370
It's nice to have such a handsome son.

528
00:45:32,370 --> 00:45:34,390
Your son is so perfect.

529
00:45:34,390 --> 00:45:38,250
What perfect?
I don't know about that.

530
00:45:39,050 --> 00:45:41,120
He is so handsome.

531
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:43,450
As much as this time...

532
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:06,060
Crazy bitch.
She thinks she some sort of queen.

533
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:09,900
It's all due to her husband and her son.
She's a loser.

534
00:46:09,900 --> 00:46:13,660
When I met her 20 years ago,
she didn't dare talk to me. What the hell.

535
00:46:13,660 --> 00:46:16,640
She graduated from an unknown university.

536
00:46:23,230 --> 00:46:26,470
I'm sorry for not telling you in advance.

537
00:46:26,470 --> 00:46:29,430
Hey. This humiliation is just for a moment.

538
00:46:30,800 --> 00:46:33,470
It can't be helped.

539
00:46:33,470 --> 00:46:36,370
We have to take extraordinary measures.
Your rank as it is...

540
00:46:36,370 --> 00:46:38,790
I'm sorry, Mom.

541
00:46:38,790 --> 00:46:40,990
Huh?

542
00:46:40,990 --> 00:46:46,560
Because I couldn't be first in the class like Hui Yeong,
you've had to humble yourself.

543
00:46:59,010 --> 00:47:00,690
Ma Hui Yeong.

544
00:47:11,460 --> 00:47:13,410
You did well.

545
00:47:13,410 --> 00:47:18,820
Although you will never see Son Jae Yeong again,
you should still tread lightly.

546
00:47:24,090 --> 00:47:26,370
You said that before.

547
00:47:27,770 --> 00:47:31,390
It is as you said, "kids like you."

548
00:47:33,370 --> 00:47:38,820
What kind of kids are the "kids like you"
that you talk about?

549
00:47:38,820 --> 00:47:40,380
That?

550
00:47:41,390 --> 00:47:43,390
That is...

551
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,520
By the way, where are you transferring to?

552
00:47:50,560 --> 00:47:53,920
Onyang. My mom works there.

553
00:47:55,590 --> 00:47:57,460
Kids like you?

554
00:47:58,820 --> 00:48:03,630
What I meant by kids like you...
Nothing much.

555
00:48:03,630 --> 00:48:07,400
Although you breathe and are living, well...

556
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:11,960
Even if you keep living on like this,
I wonder what hope there could possibly be.

557
00:48:12,900 --> 00:48:16,980
Whatever...
People who you can treat however you want?

558
00:48:19,650 --> 00:48:25,520
You just keep living on since you were thrown
out into the world without any kind of blessings.

559
00:48:25,520 --> 00:48:28,250
You're still breathing,

560
00:48:28,250 --> 00:48:30,890
so you don't have the courage to disappear.

561
00:48:33,010 --> 00:48:37,260
They are pitiful.
Kids like you.

562
00:48:47,820 --> 00:48:49,450
You?

563
00:48:52,170 --> 00:48:54,070
You're not pitiful?

564
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:05,630
Why?
I'm different from you.

565
00:49:05,630 --> 00:49:07,260
Get going.

566
00:49:11,930 --> 00:49:14,430
You said you were curious about this, too, didn't you?

567
00:49:14,430 --> 00:49:18,670
You were leaving anyway,
so I could have left you alone, so why?

568
00:49:18,670 --> 00:49:21,130
Why did I have to go that far?

569
00:49:24,440 --> 00:49:26,370
Because you offend me.

570
00:49:27,340 --> 00:49:33,050
Because you kept making issues of things when all you had
to do was just go along with it quietly and disappear.

571
00:49:34,540 --> 00:49:36,030
For me.

572
00:49:38,220 --> 00:49:40,600
Your question was answered, right?

573
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,360
All of it?

574
00:50:23,030 --> 00:50:25,290
- Yes, Mom.
- Did you pack?

575
00:50:25,290 --> 00:50:29,920
For now, pack a little bit.
I'll go to Seoul on Sunday and do it instead.

576
00:50:29,920 --> 00:50:35,790
Earlier today I went to your school, and it was nice.

577
00:50:35,790 --> 00:50:41,160
Forget it all.
Come here and let's just study hard, Joon Woo.

578
00:50:41,160 --> 00:50:46,970
You'll do well in a good university.
When I see your dad later, I'll brag about you.

579
00:50:49,690 --> 00:50:51,400
Dad?

580
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:56,800
Where is he living?
Can you contact him?

581
00:50:58,860 --> 00:51:01,040
Of course, I'm still in touch.

582
00:51:01,040 --> 00:51:06,870
I told you. Because of his company,
I heard that he's living in Pohang or somewhere.

583
00:51:06,870 --> 00:51:10,020
He's very worried about you but he can't contact you.

584
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:15,500
Mom, I'm hanging up. I'm on my way home.

585
00:51:15,500 --> 00:51:17,730
Joon Woo. Joon—

586
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:44,410
Mom, you think I don't know where he lives, right?

587
00:51:58,360 --> 00:52:02,260
I know where this person lives.

588
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:10,590
I think I have more courage since I'm about to leave,

589
00:52:10,590 --> 00:52:12,560
to see that person just once before leaving.

590
00:52:15,490 --> 00:52:20,770
The person who made me come
into the world without any good luck.

591
00:52:20,770 --> 00:52:24,260
Choi Myeong Joon.

592
00:52:26,350 --> 00:52:28,440
Who is there?

593
00:52:34,640 --> 00:52:37,800
♬ It won't do ♬

594
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:38,420
Excuse me, but...

595
00:52:38,420 --> 00:52:41,260
We haven't finished our jjajangmyeon yet.

596
00:52:41,260 --> 00:52:43,450
Tell him I'll put the dishes out in half an hour.

597
00:52:43,450 --> 00:52:45,800
We will put them out in half an hour.
(Delivery person comes back to collect crockery in Korea)

598
00:53:01,750 --> 00:53:03,950
Can I do something for you?

599
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:15,300
You...

600
00:53:18,870 --> 00:53:22,610
You don't know me?

601
00:53:23,410 --> 00:53:25,090
What?

602
00:53:26,070 --> 00:53:30,290
I think you found the wrong house.

603
00:53:31,890 --> 00:53:33,160
Dad!

604
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:35,090
Did you have fun?

605
00:54:35,190 --> 00:54:38,730
By chance, do you know Choi Myeong Joon?

606
00:54:38,730 --> 00:54:40,290
No, I don't know him.

607
00:54:40,290 --> 00:54:43,250
Alright.

608
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:51,590
By chance, do you know Choi Myeong Joon?

609
00:54:51,590 --> 00:54:55,080
Choi Myeong Joon? No.

610
00:55:04,030 --> 00:55:06,470
I thought I finally found you.

611
00:55:12,410 --> 00:55:16,990
I always thought how our first
meeting would be and what should I say.

612
00:55:18,320 --> 00:55:20,020
But...

613
00:56:19,710 --> 00:56:21,460
Yes?

614
00:56:21,460 --> 00:56:23,330
I wanted to know if you had returned home.

615
00:56:23,330 --> 00:56:26,040
Yes I did.

616
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:28,130
I'm packing my stuff now.

617
00:56:28,130 --> 00:56:33,940
Joon Woo, I'm sorry for earlier.
Mom just wanted to...

618
00:56:33,940 --> 00:56:35,890
What for?

619
00:56:37,120 --> 00:56:38,980
I will be good when I come.

620
00:56:38,980 --> 00:56:42,930
No, no. Even when you come,
don't try so hard to do things well.

621
00:56:42,930 --> 00:56:46,600
As long you are with me, I'm fine.

622
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:51,400
Women here are in a hurry to see my handsome son.

623
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:53,020
You know Hae Yeong, right?

624
00:56:53,020 --> 00:56:56,700
Today she made kimchi for your arrival.

625
00:56:56,700 --> 00:57:00,800
- And Seon Mi, you know. Seon Mi—
- Sorry, Mom.

626
00:57:01,810 --> 00:57:03,400
Huh?

627
00:57:05,120 --> 00:57:07,540
To bring problems again.

628
00:57:12,420 --> 00:57:15,040
Now, I want to be a better person.

629
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:19,790
What is this?
It's not your fault.

630
00:57:19,790 --> 00:57:22,810
It's all because of these jerk people.

631
00:57:23,510 --> 00:57:27,470
Because you do not live with your mother,
they think you are a pushover.

632
00:57:29,540 --> 00:57:34,220
Who can I blame?
It's all because of me.

633
00:57:34,220 --> 00:57:38,300
I should be right there next to you.

634
00:57:38,300 --> 00:57:41,320
Because of the money, I'm always like this.

635
00:57:41,320 --> 00:57:45,320
Mom, are you crying again?

636
00:57:45,320 --> 00:57:49,920
No, why would I?
If I'm crying, it would mean I have failed.

637
00:57:50,950 --> 00:57:57,570
And you, don't ever get down thinking
that you're running away from there, okay?

638
00:57:57,570 --> 00:58:02,300
Mom is here, so that's why you are coming to live with me.

639
00:58:03,200 --> 00:58:07,070
Let's live here happily, Joon Woo.

640
00:58:07,070 --> 00:58:13,950
Mom... Mom is really happy right now.
You know it, right? Because I can live with my son.

641
00:58:14,670 --> 00:58:18,030
I will be able to prepare your breakfast every day.

642
00:58:18,030 --> 00:58:22,090
I will also be able to take care of your school uniform.

643
00:58:24,100 --> 00:58:27,200
- I'm really happy.
- Yes.

644
00:58:29,520 --> 00:58:32,000
Oh, have a good night.

645
00:59:10,600 --> 00:59:12,760
Hey, if you do this, you're just a runner.
Do you understand?

646
00:59:12,760 --> 00:59:16,420
Yes, go away!
Go then! You're not cool at all!

647
00:59:16,420 --> 00:59:19,250
Fine! You runner!

648
00:59:19,250 --> 00:59:21,270
I'm running away.

649
00:59:21,270 --> 00:59:25,460
Why do I have to continue to run away from things?

650
00:59:25,460 --> 00:59:28,890
Why do I have to keep running away?

651
00:59:28,890 --> 00:59:32,270
Is it because somehow I do not care about my life?

652
00:59:32,270 --> 00:59:36,190
I have pity for kids like you.

653
00:59:37,420 --> 00:59:39,430
Like me?

654
00:59:51,170 --> 00:59:53,180
I'm sorry, Joon Woo.

655
00:59:53,180 --> 00:59:57,410
Because of me, because of me...

656
00:59:57,410 --> 00:59:59,600
My son, I'm really sorry.

657
01:00:01,210 --> 01:00:03,820
I'm sorry.

658
01:00:26,120 --> 01:00:29,500
Don't cry, Mom.
If you cry, I see everything.

659
01:00:37,360 --> 01:00:41,240
I'm not crying. I'm in bed right now.

660
01:00:45,490 --> 01:00:48,170
Mom is young and immature.

661
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:54,460
But she did not abandon me and flee,
although she was young.

662
01:00:56,120 --> 01:00:58,610
She didn't run away.

663
01:01:21,300 --> 01:01:24,120
Everyone, I have good news for you.

664
01:01:24,120 --> 01:01:30,580
Regarding the simulated exam,
our Hui Yeong is the first student in the ranking

665
01:01:31,580 --> 01:01:34,270
for each subject.

666
01:01:38,310 --> 01:01:39,350
Hui Yeong, you rock!

667
01:01:39,350 --> 01:01:40,680
Ma Hui Yeong!

668
01:01:40,680 --> 01:01:42,600
- Ma Hui Yeong.
- How can he be so capable?

669
01:01:42,600 --> 01:01:44,670
Right?

670
01:01:44,670 --> 01:01:47,620
- Ma Hui Yeong!
- Hui Yeong?

671
01:01:47,620 --> 01:01:49,940
You can say a few words to everyone.

672
01:01:52,880 --> 01:01:55,890
- Thank you, Teacher.
- Ah, don't mention it.

673
01:01:56,750 --> 01:01:58,420
Thank you, everyone.

674
01:01:58,420 --> 01:02:02,130
I think I did great today because I'm lucky,
but I will continue to study harder.

675
01:02:02,130 --> 01:02:04,840
Let's all do our best next time.

676
01:02:04,840 --> 01:02:07,200
Fine, applause!

677
01:02:08,690 --> 01:02:10,270
So cool!

678
01:02:15,250 --> 01:02:21,870
♬ Please don't say a word,
'cause they all left and said now ♬

679
01:02:21,870 --> 01:02:27,210
♬ Like a journey coming to an end ♬

680
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:33,570
♬ You say let it run like the river
while them without a care ♬

681
01:02:33,570 --> 01:02:44,090
♬ Just like the days
we were young and fumbling ♬

682
01:02:44,090 --> 01:02:47,350
♬ Everything fades away ♬

683
01:02:47,350 --> 01:02:50,500
♬ Let it go by with a flow ♬

684
01:02:50,500 --> 01:02:57,290
♬ I really wish I could stay, but you know me. ♬

685
01:02:57,290 --> 01:03:00,640
♬ All the moments we shared ♬

686
01:03:00,640 --> 01:03:04,330
Moment at Eighteen
~ Preview ~

687
01:03:04,330 --> 01:03:06,040
Ma Hui Yeong, don't mess with me.

688
01:03:06,040 --> 01:03:11,260
In pairs, you guys will spend 3 minutes free talking
but the learning leader will pick the pairs randomly.

689
01:03:11,260 --> 01:03:14,730
It's good that you didn't run away.

690
01:03:14,730 --> 01:03:18,530
If any problems arise just feel free to tell me.

691
01:03:18,530 --> 01:03:20,770
- Yes.
- "Yes", that conventional answer.

692
01:03:20,770 --> 01:03:23,540
If her grades, her English,
and her exams are ruined because of you,

693
01:03:23,540 --> 01:03:28,050
I don't think it's something someone like you could deal with.
Not for your but for Soo Bin's sake.

694
01:03:28,050 --> 01:03:31,540
Why are you even thinking of me?
Because I'm weaker? Because I look pitiful?

695
01:03:31,540 --> 01:03:34,400
Okay. I guess Joon Woo isn't who I thought he was.

696
01:03:39,930 --> 01:03:44,840
♬ Everything fades away. Just go with the flow. ♬
